text:
This place is HUGE!!!
I like me some hot dogs and the Varsity does it up good. Good chili, no beans and the toasted buns remind me of the old Canteen's grilled hot dogs at home. I liked the Onion rings and my buddy had a chocolate shake - he wasn't impressed.
Uhm, let me just go and take my $3 to Trader Joe's or Berkeley Bowl.  I can get more food for the $3.

This is officially my favorite Nordstrom in the bay area. I love that I can always find my size in whatever I'm looking for. For the most part, I shop in the Juniors section, but I also like hitting up Topshop and the shoe section, of course.

I had the sweetest girl help me in the Juniors section, her name was Mikaela (not sure I spelled that right). She helped me and my friend from start to finish while helping all the other customers too! 

She rang us up quickly while making great conversation. I felt so taken care of.

Although Nordstrom isn't the cheapest place to shop, I absolutely love its styles and service. I would shop here much more often if I had the financial backing to do so!

Love this place! Awesome quality and prices are reasonable! They let you negotiate the price and the owner and staff are very polite. I bought a fantastic red sweater dress that was prime vintage, to wear at a fund raising event at @ Saks store. I will return to this store each time I come to town.

Great place to bring the family for a quick sweet snack. Ice cream sandwiches with fresh cookies. So many combination's to choose from, it's like the Subway of Ice Cream Sandwiches. I personally love the Chocolate Cookie with White Chocolate Chips paired with the Cookies and Cream Ice Cream. Although the line may look long at times, they serve their customers pretty fast. Regardless, you can never go wrong with the price of $1.50 for a premium  ice cream sandwich.

I've been to Joe's maybe three or four times and i've never had a problem or complaint. 
On my last outing, I had their filet w/mash and mushroom gravy. The filet was perfectly cooked and was of excellent quality. Being that it was a10 oz filet, the price was about 23 dollars which actually is quite reasonable when compared to some other establishments in the Providence area. The service has always been average, never above and beyond but also never bad. 
You will most likely have to park in the Providence Place mall which will run you a buck for the first three hours. It's an especially nice joint to eat at during the summer. That is when they open all of the street side windows. 
As far as decor goes. It's a rather elegant place that manages to look sophisticated without being overly stuffy and off putting. 
I highly recommend Joe's to any and everyone. Whether you're looking for a simple burger or a 10 oz filet. Joe's has you covered.
